# Banking APIs

This specification defines the APIs for Data Holders exposing Banking endpoints.

```diff
Changes to Banking endpoints to accommodate NBL and BNPL. Updated versions are: 
+ Get Products v5
+ Get Product Detail v7
+ Get Accounts v3
+ Get Account Detail v5
+ Get Bulk Balances v2
+ Get Bulk Direct Debits v2
+ Get Scheduled Payments Bulk v3
+ Get Transactions For Account v2
+ Get Transaction Detail v3
+ Get Instalment Plans for Account v1
+ Get Instalment Plans Bulk v1

The `BUY_NOW_PAY_LATER` value has been added as an option for the 'product-category' query parameter in the below endpoints:
 - Get Products
 - Get Accounts
 - Get Bulk Balances
 - Get Bulk Direct Debits
 - Get Scheduled Payments Bulk
+ BUY_NOW_PAY_LATER

The `BUY_NOW_PAY_LATER` value has been added as an option for the 'productCategory' property in the below endpoints:
 - Get Products
 - Get Product Detail
 - Get Accounts
 - Get Account Detail
+ BUY_NOW_PAY_LATER

The 'instalments' object has been added to the below endpoints:
 - Get Product Detail
 - Get Account Detail
+ instalments

The `EXTRA_DOWN_PAYMENT` featureType has been added and the `EXTRA_REPAYMENTS` featureType description updated, applicable to the below endpoints:
 - Get Product Detail
 - Get Account Detail
+ EXTRA_DOWN_PAYMENT

New field added to the below endpoints:
 - Get Accounts
 - Get Account Detail
+ isInstalmentDetailAvailable

New field added to the below endpoints:
 - Get Transactions
 - Get Transaction Detail
+ instalmentPlanId

Updated the description of the tiers field in BankingProductDepositRateV2 and BankingProductLendingRateV3
- Rate tiers applicable for this rate.
+ Qualifying criteria or conditions relevant to the associated rate.

Added default field value to the schema specification for the following fields: 
 - BankingBalance > creditLimit
 - BankingBalance > amortisedLimit
 - BankingScheduledPaymentInterval > dayInInterval

Applied consistent wording to conditional field statements (detailed in Maintenance issue #683).
```

